Colony Bankcorp, Inc. Key Developments

Colony Bankcorp, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Reports Net Loan Charge-Offs for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 18 17
Colony Bankcorp, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net interest income of $9,816,000 compared to $9,525,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $3,590,000 compared to $3,169,000 a year ago. Net income was $2,433,000 compared to $2,167,000 a year ago. Net income available to common shareholders was $2,433,000 or $0.28 per diluted share compared to $1,761,000 or $0.21 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Common book value per share was $10.55 compared to $10.12 a year ago. Tangible common book value per share was $10.54 compared to $10.11 a year ago. Return on average assets was 0.81% compared to 0.61% a year ago. Return on average total equity was 11.10% compared to 6.99% a year ago. Net interest income after provision for loan losses was $9,816,000 compared to $9,171,000 a year ago. 



For the six months, the company reported net interest income of $19,278,000 compared to $18,981,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $6,709,000 compared to $6,208,000 a year ago. Net income was $4,550,000 compared to $4,228,000 a year ago. Net income available to common shareholders was $4,339,000 or $0.50 per diluted share compared to $3,417,000 or $0.40 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Common book value per share was $10.55 compared to $10.12 a year ago. Tangible common book value per share was $10.54 compared to $10.11 a year ago. Return on average assets was 0.72% compared to 0.59% a year ago. Return on average total equity was 9.56% compared to 6.87% a year ago.


For the second quarter ended June 30, 2017, the company’s net loan charge-offs of $821,000 compared to $513,000 a year ago.


Colony Bankcorp, Inc. Declares Second Quarter Dividend, Payable on June 30, 2017
May 24 17
Colony Bankcorp, Inc. announced that its Board of Directors declared a second quarterly cash dividend of $0.025 per share payable June 30, 2017 to shareholders of record on June 02, 2017.


Colony Bankcorp Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Reports Net Charge-Offs for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 19 17
Colony Bankcorp Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net income available to shareholders of $1,906,000, or $0.22 per diluted share compared to $1,656,000 or $0.20 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net interest income was $9,462,000 compared to $9,456,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $3,119,000 compared to $3,039,000 a year ago. Net income was $2,117,000 compared to $2,061,000 a year ago. Common book value per share was $10.17 against $9.78 reported a year ago. Tangible common book value per share was $10.17 against $9.77 reported a year ago. Return on average assets was 0.63% against 0.57% and return on average total equity was 8.11% against 6.75% reported a year ago.

For the quarter, the company's net charge-offs were $394,000, or 0.05% of average loans.


